definition.value: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 6 by a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 3 by a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group.
A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of 2-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucopyranuronic acid and 2,5-anhydro-D-glucitol joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylglucose consisting of alpha-D-galactopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
